For all of you that wanted to design these instruments of destruction, 
but never got around to it...

I spent a few hours last night designing an rough skeleton of the Death 
Star and the Star Destroyer (well, a Super Star Destroyer: a Star 
Destroyer is only about 1 milion Disp).

First, I had to extend the hull table to accomodate these monsters...

       Displacement      Kilolitres       MV            Length
        (Millions)       (Millions)

SSDestr   100               1,400         60 524        1 388 metres
D. Star  6400              89,600    247 906 978       88 833 metres

Then I installed a jumpdrive, jump6 for the SSDestroyer, jump2 for the 
Death Star...

Jump6, TL F    Volume       Mass            Cr        Surface Area       
              (Millions)   (Millions)   (Trillions)    (Millions)
SSDestr          98          196           29.4           32.667

Jump2, TL F

Death Star      1,792        3,584        537.6          5,973.333

[note: the surface area for the Super Star Destroyer is about half of 
it\'s total surface area!  This may pose problems for the future, and 
indicate why it\'s most powerful weaponry is high-powered lasers.  And you 
can probably forget either Contra-grav (not missed) or EMM (definitely 
missed, but then again, you don\'t expect this ship to _hide_, do you?)]

Weaponry

No, I didn\'t do this part.  However, I suspect that the Super Star 
Destroyer\'s top armorment would be lasers measured in the million\'s of 
joules.  As for the Death Star... well, it can certainly blow up a small 
moon, but even with a meson gun worthy of deathless fame throughout the 
ages, the best it can do to a Earth-sized planet is slowly strip off it\'s 
crust.

To get firepower of sufficent magnitude, what you need is probably a 
disintergrater gun of legendary dimensions.  However, I lack hard data on 
the force needed to blow up a planet ("how many hit\'s can a planet 
take?"), or the neccessary info to build this gun.  Any takers? 

Power Plant

I have no idea of the power consumption needed by these beasties, so I 
decreed that that the powerplant is 3% of the total volume (the 
powerplant for Steve Bonnevilles\' _Azhanti High Lightling_ is 5%, but TL F 
powerplants are twice as efficent).

              Volume           Mass              MW              Cr
            (Millions)      (Millions)        (Billions)     (Trillions)

SSDestr         42             84               .252             8.4
Death Star    2,668          5,336             16.008          533.6

Engineering Crew (assuming TL F computers)
  Super Star Destroyer            1,680,000
  Death Star                    106,720,000

Estimated Ship crew (\'Engineering crew x 3\' is my rule of thumb)
  Super Star Destroyer            5,040,000
  Death Star                    320,160,000

Estimated Cost (Power Plant cost x 5)
  Super Star Destroyer             42 TCr
  Death Star                    2,668 TCr

.. Now, about feasibility.

Assuming every Hi-Pop system can pay 5 TCr of the bill for a Super Star 
Destroyer (ie. money that would have been earmarked for five Trillion Credit 
Squadrons, of four ship\'s each), you would need 8.4 Hi-Pop systems to 
build a SSD, and 33.6 Hi-Pop systems to build a squadron of four.  Now, 
because a typical Imperial Sector (a *Third* Imperial Sector:) has  
between 30-40 Hi-Pop systems, a Sector Duke would be trading his 1,000 
ship Navy for a squadron of near-invinsible warships (imagine trying to 
get a critical hit on these babies!).  Pleasing to the ego, but not sane 
military strategy.

As for the Death Star... well, remarkably enough, the Third Imperium 
*can* build it (THAT\'s how big the Third Imperium is!).  Not only that, 
but it could do so without touching the Imperial Navy! (you can kiss 
goodbye to the Planetary (non-jump) warships and IISS, however.)

You need 2668 TCr to build one; that is, 533.6 Hi-Pop systems.  Now, 
since the entire Imperium only contains about 880 Hi-Pop systems, you 
would be using 60.6% of your Naval budget to build this technological 
monstrosity.  The entire Imperial Navy, with it\'s roughly 42,000 major 
ships, 126,000 minor ships and 20 Naval Depots is worth about 3000 TCr.  
But \'the _other_ Imperial Navy\', the Planetary squadrons and the 
Imperial Scouts,  are also worth 3000 TCr.  Guess who\'s budget disappear\'s?

Of course, you can just stick to Star Destroyers.  At 1 Million 
displacement, they are twice the size of the current Imperial 
heavyweight, the 500 kiloton _Tigress_ Dreadnaught\'s.  Moreover, they 
won\'t cause the Sector Minister of Finance to stir restlessly in 
sweat-filled nightmares.  Perhaps someone here would like to try his 
hand in building one...?

Alvin Plummer
(Supervisor, Imperial Naval Yards (Endor)) 

