Hi all,

I just finished a novel which I thought other Traveller fans
may find enjoyable.

The book is 

The War Machine, Crisis of Empire III by
Roger MacBride Allen and David Drake

Now normally I\'m not a big fan of David Drake (apart from
the first Hammer\'s Slammers, I\'ve never thought he was very 
original or insightful. I bought this one used and didn\'t 
hae high expectations. I was impressed with it and read it 
quickly over two nights. 

The book covers several topics of interest to the TML. Discussions
of jump mechanics, insystem jumps, fleet combat, and ancient 
virus-like aliens are included in a standard space opera setting. 

I don\'t know if it is still in print. I read volume III without 
reading I or II and it wasn\'t diminished. 

The novel reminded me of The Mote in God\'s Eye (one of my all-time
favorites) but with more of a traveller feel. This was TNE at its
best. Several plot devices have long been staples in my campaign
(which I won\'t discuss here to prevent spoilers).

TTFN,

Glenn

