The Jonkereen are a "Home-made" Minor human species.  They were detailed in
(as I recall) the MegaTraveller\'s Journal #3 (or maybe #2) and were
genetically modified by the Imperial Colonial Authority, or some such, to be
well adapted to desert conditions.  After several generations they are doing
fairly well, although their culture is only TL 3 or 4.  I seem to remember
that they had, in turn, several small settlements on other nearby
"Moisturally challenged" Domain o\' Deneb worlds.  As I recall, they were
somewhat reminiscent of the Beduin in terms of culture.  Nice Vilardi
illustrations for the article, too.

No rules for designing one (probably "Barbarian" from the MT or CT career
types) and no naming conventions were provided.

I don\'t have the article with me, being at work, so I can\'t be more
specific.  Doubtless, hordes of others will  respond more accurately.  Well,
maybe one horde.

