Clothing is either ill-fitting civvies or worn military fatigues.  Has a 
thick Denebi accent when he speaks, which is seldom..Sticks close to the 
Adept in the field.

Personality: Laconic.  No longer beat\'s up people on impulse, but is 
still tempted.  Despite his distain for authority he is loyal to his 
order and his God, and is both quick-witted and fearless in action.

His great goal is to obtain fame and renoun, to cleanse his name and be a 
hero to his people, `to sieze the Glory\'.  His every action, every though 
is directed to this one goal.

History: Born in Deneb, Suvarov\'s childhood dream was to join the Regency 
Marines.  He served two tours in the Marines with distinction, obtaining 
several citations and metals, including the Regent\'s Star for 
spearheading an attack on a nasty enemy strongpoint in 1194.

All that he worked for was lost when he callously murdered a 
non-combatent on the battlefield in 1196.  Although his unit didn\'t report
this crime to the authorities, rumour\'s about his action eventually reached
an officer, who set court-marshal proceedings in motion.  Because of his
previous heroism Suvarov wasn\'t shot: instead he was given 100 lashes with a
neurowhip and dishonourably cashiered, with his life savings paid out to
the victim\'s wife as restitution.

Without honour, without his friends, and without a future, Suvorov would 
soon have destroyed himself in drugs or drink if he wasn\'t rescued by a 
compassionate priest.  After repenting of his sins, paying penance, and 
converting into the Imperial Church, he requested and, after careful testing
using Zhodani techniques, was allowed to join the M.O.C.

His sterling record with the M.O.C. has finally landed his first 
independent assignment, with Adept Flourentine: an opportunity to prove 
himself a reformed Christian that Suvarov has been waiting for.


