rather stilted.  Her style of dress is definitely unknown by local Aslans 
(and human Aslan watchers).

Personality: Beyond the usual Aslan formality and pride, Kyuiwei is 
incredibly curious ("as curious as a Hiver" is the Regency stereotype: 
of course, Kyuiwei would immediately ask to see a real live one).  
Everything she sees must be poked, tested, sampled and analyzed.  Enev 
more interesting for an Aslan, she applies her curiouisity to sentinents 
- regard less of their barbaric (ie non-Aslan) culture, she just must 
find out more about them.  her non-judgemental attitude - very rare on 
her world, where no human has been seen since the Rebellion started - has 
marked her out as her clan\'s Ambassator Extraordinare.

History: After graduating from a local "university", Kyuiwei was selected 
to join her clan\'s scientific community as a field scout/scientist.  As 
scientisis were the subgroup most likely to interact with the Strangers 
(ie. Aslans outside of the Yekhakteal clan) she became exposed to these 
folk, and - unlike her peers - wrote about these strange Aslans with 
their peculiar habits for the general public.

Worldwide fame and notoriety was produced: the government initally 
attempted to discourage further writings, but, under pressure from 
acadamia, business, and her hordes of fans, relented, and gave her funds 
to continue exploring.  And explore she did: with an aged trader with a 
questionable jump drive she explored first her subsector, then the entire 
sector, taking odd jobs and speculating on cargo to keep food in the 
belly and the engines hot.

When she returned "to stay", she had not only bought a treasure trove of 
information, but had inadvertantly laid the groundwork for other clan members
to follow, both business and scientists.  This led to a surge in the ecomony
(Yekhaktei is the highest tech system in the subsector), which led to a 
vastly increased government interest in her explorations.

Eventually, the clan leaders managed to persuade her to launch another 
one-ship expedition, but as a formally accreddited ambassador of her 
clan.  She was given the _Ouhaei Hteftaihwoarl_, a gorgeous TL E Aslan 
scout/diplomatic yacht, with a read lab, probes, RCV equipment and 
everything, wrapped in a million credts worht of luxurious fittings, 
double-large rooms, whirlpool, etc.  And she was given a \'loose\'itenary, 
involving contacting all the major clans of the Hierate, the Zhodani, and 
the Regency.

Kyuiwei has spent the last eight years away from her distant home, and 
has seen more wonders than anyone else in her clan\'s history.  Now 
completing her tour in the Zhodani Consulate, she\'s now in Chronor 
subsector, preparing to enter the Spinward Marches.  With most of her 
experiences of humans from the Consulate, she would be initally very 
truthful and trusting, expecting the truth in return. However, her view
of the Regency will be as an inferior civilization, full of liars and 
mentally ill people (as her Zhodani friends suggest).  Indeed, one of her 
crew is a Zho \'guide\' (actually a SORAG agent), sent specifically to 
protect her from the Regency barbarians.


