    'topic' => 'Solomani in my universe',
    'body' => 'Some point for clarrification:

1) This is how I\'m justifying why Terrans don\'t like the phrase "Solomani",
even though they created the phrase: during the occupation of Earth by the
Imperium, "Solomani" became a durogatory phrase. Words do, after all, change
connotation. And, yes, Terrans still consider themselves racially superior
to Vilani - I can\'t think of any idea why they wouldn\'t.

2) There\'s a reason why the Terrans cut themselves off. After the Occupation
of Terra, the Terrans naturally could not stand being controlled by
"inferior Vilani", and declared war on the Imperium.
They staged several rebellions and various other
"subversive" and "terrorist" activities. Of course, the Imperium was just a
wee bit PISSED OFF about this, and there was a great military prescence in
that subsector.

After the Imperium fell, much of that military prescence was disbanded, and
the Terrans were able to "Drive out" any stragglers. However, Terra and
the surrounding area was devestated, and the Terrans needed time to rebuild.
When Virus came, the Terrans were still in the early stages of rebuilding
their area of space. Since they were rebuilding virtually everything - and
that includes replacing destroyed or worn out electronic equipment and
starships, Terran scientists were able to recognize Virus as a problem and
deal with it.

One more point about Virus: the Terrans still have a bit of a racial
superiority
complex and would be damned before recognizing Virus as a living entity.

As always, I will solicit any comments.
