    'topic' => 'Regency Alien\'s.',
    'body' => '
This list of Regency Aliens is a chopped-up varient of an earlier work I 
have found, originally written by Mitchell K. Schwartz.

Local sentient\'s - major races:

Humaniti - Solomani, Vilani, Zhodani
Vargr - (someone with the correct sourcebook, please name the major races 
         of Vargr, and where they are... thanks.)
         One major branch is known to me... the Urzaeng, as big as the 
         Aslan, though not as smart. (Bred by the Ancients as guards).  
         Throughout the Vargr Extents.
K\'Kree - there is one contient of a Regency world (names?), which is the 
         home of diplomatic K\'Kree stranded in the Regency.  Apparently, 
         they have managed to form a company of some kind , (in 
         entertainment or  starship construction?)
Droyne - are on about 20 worlds in the marches, and about 15 elsewhere
         in the Regency.
Hivers - there are none.
Aslan - there are lot\'s of them, esp in the rimward regions of the Regency.
        Most Aslan Subjects of the Regent would be considered outcasts by 
        their Hierate brethern.  Would someone here do a nice write-up of 
        Regency Aslan, please? (I would do it myself, but lack the 
        Solimani & Aslan book)

Minor races 

Humaniti: 

Daryen (ex-Darrian\'s) - Daryen/Spinward Marches 0627
           See Aliens 8: Daryens (seem remarkably elf-like: 
           forest-dwelling, pointed ears, etc.)

Foriani - Floria/Trojan Reaches 0213
          Made up of two castes, the Barnai (top) and the Feskals (Bottom).
          See TD 20.

Halkans - Halka/Trojan Reach 0510
          "Halkans appear to be slightly built albinos, but they are 
          not.  Their eyes are pale grey (nearly white).  Their hair color 
          ranges from white to ash-pale blond.  Discovered by Florian 
          explorers in -50 ti, they were held as slaves untol 1000\'s.  See 
          TD 19.

Jonkeereen - Jonkeer/Deneb 1324
          "Geneered race [by the Imperial Ministry of Colonialization], 
          designed for desert existance.  Originally designed for a desert 
          planet on Gushmege to counter Suerrat expansion in the 500s and 
          400s, they were developed by SUSag on Jonkeer in the 500s and 
          developed their own subculture in the 600s.  See MTJ3."

Nexies - Nexine/Spinward Marches 3030
         "Nexine is an underpopulated water world being "reseeded" by the 
         Ministry of Conservation (as of 1105) using biologically altered 
         humans.  No description available.  See Supplement 3 Spinward 
         Marches."

Syleans - Sylea/Core
         "Human minor race responsible for the Sylean Federation, which 
         became the Third Imperium" {Probably overrepresented in the 
         Regency Nobility.}

Tapazmal - Dlaekan/Reft 3134 (the Wild side of Reft sector)
         "Geneered by the Ancients for low birth rate, later raided by 
         the Loeskalth before annexation by the Zira Sirku.  See TD20."

Other: 
 
Bwaps/Newts - Found throughout the Regency, and was once common 
              throughout Imperial space.  Amphibious, very good bureaucrats.

Ebokin - Based on Yebab/Spinward Marches 2202.
         "Arthopod octoped sophonts living mostly planet-bound on this 
          one planet at TL 5."  See the Traveller Adventure

Gl\'lu - Kubishush/Deneb 0917
        "Heraphroditic septapodal minor race.  See TD1."
        (A little more info would be nice, for those who don\'t have TD1)

Keo Neseb  -  Penkwar/Spinward Marches 2128
         "Extinct insectoid race resembling giant praying mantises. 
         Believed to have reached their apex about 8 million years ago, 
         having reached at least two neighbors Persephone and Harvosette. 
         See RICE paper on Persephone."

Larianz - Byret/Spinward Marches 2523
         See Spinward Marches Campagin (again, more info for us latecomers
         would be appreciated.)

Llellewyloly - Junidy/Spinward Marches 3202
         Large plant-like people. (Moble?) Population about 14 billion in 
         the early 1100\'s. Nicknames Dandies. See Traveller adventure.

Salika - Garden/Reft 0435
         "Humanoid race evolved to be aquatic, covered in short fine fur 
         like a seal, with slightly webbed multi-jointed fingers. The Salika 
         abandoned their home world in generation ships when their sun went 
         through a hot phase about 1000 ti. Friendly and tolerant, not 
         prone to combat. They live only 45-55 standard years. See TD19&20."

Shi\'awei - Chaosheo/Deneb 0130 
         "Bulky aquatic creatures; bullet shaped with 4 evenly spaced 
         arms. See TD19."

Shreikers - 567-908/Spinward Marches 1031
          "Intelligent hexapods about 1 m at the shoulder. They talk at the 
          high end of human hearing, hence their name. Achieved TL3 before a
          planetary tectonic disaster shook them back down to TL0. See 
          Adventure 11 Safari Ship."

Tentrassi - Origin unknown
          "The Tentrassi wander space in nomad jump fleets, seeking their 
          lost home world. Nomad Fleet 8 visited Raweh (Spinward Marches 
          0137) around 1100 and again in 1122 ti. See MTJ3." 
          (Any info on tech levels?)



