    'body' => 'Morning all,

Thought I\'d take a few moments out from writing my U-Beaut Sector
Viewer/Generator to post a quick design:

TL 14 Meson Gun (Solomani)

Bore:           4.58 m
Power Required: 69.4 MW
Volume:         2383 m^3
Mass:           2291 t
Length:         120 m

Damage: Short 5:240 Medium 10:118 Long 20:60 Extreme 40:30

Crew:           5
Price:          MCr 203.32

Specs include integral Homopolar Generator and Beam Pointer (both at TL-14).

The MG-120/3 was the standard Light Meson Gun in the Solomani Confederal
Navy.  It was produced in large numbers for a number of Light Cruiser
designs, most notably the \'Malkop\' Class Light Cruiser (10000t).  The Malkop
was produced in great numbers by the Solomani as both a line warship and
commerce raider.

Two Malkop Class ships have been recovered by the Commonwealth.  The
\'Voronezh\', now the AME-0034 \'Jean d\'Arc\', entered service with the Medoci
Navy (Aquitaine) after a lengthy refit in 1199, while the \'Polyarny\' is
undergoing restoration in orbit around Teucer for the Royal Teuceri Navy
(the \'Polyarny\' is expected to be renamed TE-0011 \'Prince Nomura\'.

Reports from CEF missions suggest that at least one Malkop Class cruiser is
in the hands of a potentially hostile power, based spinward of the Near
Bootes Commonwealth.
Michael Bailey (pd82495@wapol.gov.au)

